article.headline: Long Island 74, Monmouth, N.J. 71
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- James Williams scored 17 points -- one of four Long Island players in double figures -- to lead the Blackbirds to a 74-71 win over Monmouth on Thursday. Tyrone Mattison added 15 points for Long Island (4-4, 1-0 Northeast Conference), while Eugene Kotorobai had 12 points and Aubin Scott finished with 10. Jhamar Youngblood had a game-high 20 points for the Hawks (3-7, 0-1), while Marques Alston added 13 points and Dejan Delic had 12. Long Island was in command for most of the game and held several double-digit leads, but Monmouth fought back in the second half and only trailed 72-69 when Whitney Coleman hit a 3-pointer with 1:09 left. Williams then hit a quick basket, but Youngblood answered with a driving score to trim the lead to 74-71 with 48.2 seconds left. Mattison then missed a shot in the closing seconds, but Coleman's desperation 3-point attempt at the buzzer went long.
